----------------------------------------------------------------------
README
----------------------------------------------------------------------

This default example creates an internal mesh with smooth topographic interfaces.

TO RUN:

0. Read the user manual in SPECFEM2D/doc/manual_SPECFEM2D.pdf

1. in SPECFEM2D root directory, configure, e.g., 
   ./configure FC=gfortran

2. compile:
   make all

3. cd EXAMPLES/simple_topography_and_also_a_simple_fluid_layer

4. execute script to run mesher and solver for the PSV case:
   ./run_this_example.sh

5. check out the output files in the local directory OUTPUT_FILES

----------------------------------------------------------------------


note: for convenience, a second parameter file DATA/Par_file_with_PML is provided
      which changes the setup to use PMLs. 

      it is the same setup as given in the package root DATA/ directory.
      in order to run this modified setup, just:

      > cp DATA/Par_file_with_PML DATA/Par_file

      and rerun the above steps (mainly 4. and 5.)



